---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const problems = [
	{
		label: 'clarity',
		line: 'A good idea nobody can explain well enough for anyone to use it.',
	},
	{
		label: 'systems',
		line: "A process that only works because it's stuck in one person's head.",
	},
	{
		label: 'communication',
		line: "Someone excellent at their work who's terrible at describing why.",
	},
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Home" description="Brandon DeVere builds stories and systems that help people understand complicated things well enough to actually use them.">
	<section class="container section home">
		<div class="hero">
			<h1>I build stories and systems that help people understand complicated things well enough to actually use them.</h1>
			<p class="subhead">AI is one of the tools I use to do that. It isn't the point.</p>
			<p>
				Most of my career has looked like different jobs: hospitality, real estate, recruiting, podcasting.
				Underneath, it's been the same work, taking something complicated and making it usable, then documenting
				it well enough that it doesn't have to be re-explained every time. The clearest proof of that is below.
			</p>
		</div>

		<ul class="problems">
			{problems.map((p) => (
				<li>
					<p class="meta">{p.label}</p>
					<p>{p.line}</p>
				</li>
			))}
		</ul>

		<div class="next">
			<p>
				The <a href="/work/ai-editorial-workflow">AI Editorial Workflow</a> case study is the clearest example of
				how this plays out: the actual problem, what I tried, what I got wrong, and what I'd change next time.
				AI shows up in it, but it's not really what the case study is about.
			</p>
			<p>
				Curious how hospitality, real estate, recruiting, and podcasting all led to the same place?
				That's the <a href="/about">About</a> page.
			</p>
			<p>
				If you just want the facts, the <a href="/resume">Resume</a> has them.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.hero h1 {
		max-width: 20ch;
		font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
	}

	.subhead {
		color: var(--color-ink-muted);
		font-size: 1.125rem;
	}

	.problems {
		list-style: none;
		margin: var(--space-2xl) 0 0;
		padding: 0;
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: var(--space-lg);
	}

	.problems li p:last-child {
		max-width: none;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.problems {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: var(--space-md);
		}
	}

	.next {
		margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
	}

	.next p {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
	}
</style>
